'''Xətai''' (also, '''Khatai''' and '''Khetayi''', known as '''Sovetabad''' until 2000)<ref>[http://e-qanun.az/files/framework/data/0/f_649.htm Azərbaycan Respublikasının bəzi rayonlarının inzibati ərazi bölgüsündə qismən dəyişikliklər edilməsi haqqında] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130722210537/http://e-qanun.az/files/framework/data/0/f_649.htm |date=July 22, 2013 }}</ref> is a village in the [[Babek Rayon]] of the [[Nakhchivan Autonomous Republic]] of [[Azerbaijan]].

==Etymology==
Its previous name was ''Sovetabad''. It was established in the meaning of "Soviet village" during the years of [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] power. Since 2000, the village was named '''Xətai''' (Khatai) in honor of the notable Azerbaijani statesman and poet [[Shakh Ismail Khatai]], founder of the [[Safavid dynasty|Azerbaijani Safavid State]].<ref>''Encyclopedic Dictionary of Azerbaijan Toponyms''. In two volumes. Volume I. p. 304. Baku: "East-West". 2007. {{ISBN|978-9952-34-155-3}}.</ref>

